'''Ioan Dragomir''' (11 October 1905, [[Arini<U+015F>]] <U+2013> 25 April 1985, [[Bucharest]]) was a clandestine bishop of the [[Romanian Church United with Rome, Greek-Catholic|Romanian Church united with Rome]], who worked in the prohibited [[Greek Catholic Diocese of Maramure<U+015F>|Diocese of Maramure<U+015F>]] during the [[Communist Romania|communist regime]].
 
In 1948 he was the Greek Catholic dean in [[Satu Mare]]. He was arrested for the first time in April 1948.<ref>Cicerone Ioni<U+021B>oiu, [http://www.procesulcomunismului.com/marturii/fonduri/ioanitoiu/biserici/preoti_greco_catolici_1/preoti_greco_catolici_1.pdf ''Procesul comunismului: Preo<U+021B>ii greco-catolici''], p. 7. {{ro icon}}</ref>
 
On 19 December 1964 he ordained [[Lucian Mure<U+0219>an]] (later archbishop and cardinal) as priest, and in 1965 he ordained Alexandru Mesian, later bishop of [[Greek Catholic Diocese of Lugoj|Lugoj]].

